\f0\b\fs44 \cf2 \cb1 2. Project Overview\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs40 \cf2 2.1 Background\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs32 \cf2 The current Backlog Orchestrator processes Excel-based offshore inspection data through 7 CrewAI discipline agents. While effective, the system is monolithic - all agents run within a single process, limiting interoperability and scalability.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs40 \cf2 2.2 Problem Statement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs32 \cf2 The existing architecture presents several constraints:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 No Standard Discovery:
\f2\b0 \'a0Other systems cannot discover agent capabilities\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Framework Lock-in:
\f2\b0 \'a0Agents cannot communicate with non-CrewAI systems\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Monolithic Scaling:
\f2\b0 \'a0All agents must scale together\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Limited Orchestration:
\f2\b0 \'a0Routing logic is hardcoded\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 No Reusability:
\f2\b0 \'a0Agents cannot be called independently by external clients\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

